    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "77254af4_933beed0",
        "filename": "include/private/SkFixed.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 99,
      "author": {
        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-09T15:09:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I think this code just predates ARMv8.  There they\u0027ve dropped #defines for things that are guaranteed, like __ARM_NEON__, __ARM_VFPV3__, __ARM_VFPV4__.\n\nI think we\u0027ll be good with just\n\n  #if defined(__ARM_VFPV3__)\n\nhere, or\n\n  #if defined(__ARM_VFPV3__) || defined(__aarch64__)\n\nif you want to try folding in ARMv8 at the same time.  Let\u0027s not care about GCC.",
      "parentUuid": "db1a9f8a_83a356b9",
      "revId": "c55a7d648b6e318b71a1b2b88b67e16ca9215a36",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fd502fe9_178f8699",
        "filename": "include/private/SkFixed.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 99,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-09T16:00:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m fine with that solution, but that will disable this optimization for armv7 in Google3.\n\nAny reason to prefer SK_CPU_ARM64 vs. __aarch64__?",
      "parentUuid": "77254af4_933beed0",
      "revId": "c55a7d648b6e318b71a1b2b88b67e16ca9215a36",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7d7f7da8_8a318966",
        "filename": "include/private/SkFixed.h",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 99,
      "author": {
        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-09T16:09:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m happy to sign off on that.  We really don\u0027t want to have to care about performance on GCC or MSVC anymore.\n\nNo, no big difference between SK_CPU_ARM64 and __aarch64__.  __aarch64__ is the real deal, and SK_CPU_ARM64 is just there to work around some old bug in someone\u0027s toolchain.  I don\u0027t think we need SK_BUILD_NO_OPTS anymore.",
      "parentUuid": "fd502fe9_178f8699",
      "revId": "c55a7d648b6e318b71a1b2b88b67e16ca9215a36",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
